---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout theme="light" showThemeToggle={true} title="Legal | Quincy So">
  <article>
    <header class="article-header">
      <h1>Legal</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Glossary of terms used across Quincy So project policies.</p>
    </header>

    <!-- ── GLOSSARY ─────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <h2>Glossary</h2>
    <dl class="glossary">
      <dt id="glossary-operator">Operator</dt>
      <dd>The individual or entity responsible for running a service, bot, or website — in this context, Quincy So.</dd>

      <dt id="glossary-instance">Instance</dt>
      <dd>A specific running copy of software (e.g., a Freesona bot). Different instances may have different operators, configurations, and policies.</dd>

      <dt id="glossary-third-party-service">Third-Party Service</dt>
      <dd>An external API, platform, or provider used to process requests or deliver functionality. Examples include AI models, hosting providers, and analytics services.</dd>

      <dt id="glossary-personal-data">Personal Data</dt>
      <dd>Information that can identify an individual, such as messages, usernames, server IDs, or interaction logs.</dd>

      <dt id="glossary-data-retention">Data Retention</dt>
      <dd>How long collected information is stored before being deleted or anonymized.</dd>

      <dt id="glossary-service-availability">Service Availability</dt>
      <dd>The uptime and reliability of a service. "As is" means no guarantees are made about continuous operation.</dd>

      <dt id="glossary-limitation-of-liability">Limitation of Liability</dt>
      <dd>A legal clause stating the operator is not responsible for damages, data loss, or issues arising from use of the service.</dd>

      <dt id="glossary-indemnification">Indemnification</dt>
      <dd>Your agreement to hold the operator harmless against claims or damages resulting from your use of the service.</dd>
    </dl>

    <hr />

    <!-- ── POLICY INDEX ─────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <h2>Policies</h2>
    <p>These are the current active policies. The glossary above defines key terms used throughout.</p>

    <ul>
      <li><a href="/privacy-policy/freesona">Freesona Privacy Policy</a> — How your information is collected and used for Freesona-based bot instances operated by Quincy So.</li>
      <li><a href="/terms-of-service/freesona">Freesona Terms of Service</a> — Rules governing the use of Freesona Discord bot instances operated by Quincy So.</li>
    </ul>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>